Rajgad Fort Rajgad (literal meaning Ruling Fort) is a Hill region fort situated in the Pune district of Maharashtra, India. Formerly known as Murumbdev, the fort was the first capital of the Maratha Empire under the rule of Chhatrapati Shivaji for almost 26 years, after which the capital was moved to the Raigad Fort. The most popular attraction types near Rajgad Fort are: Historic Sites Castles Caverns and Caves Waterfalls Points of Interest and Landmarks
